        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 2:25PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 225 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Pocahontas, or 12 miles south of Bolivar. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pocahontas, Middleton, Hornsby, Brownfield, Rogers Springs, Hebron,
Lisbon, Lacy, and Essary Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
